    {
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "overview",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Overview",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "Only entities with a ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.RealityKit/documentation/RealityKit/PhysicsBodyComponent",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "and a ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.RealityKit/documentation/RealityKit/CollisionComponent",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "can participate in a scene’s physics simulation.",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "If you need to move an entity that participates",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "in the physics system, it also needs a ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.RealityKit/documentation/RealityKit/PhysicsMotionComponent",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": ".",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "Add a physics body component to an entity by adopting the ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.RealityKit/documentation/RealityKit/HasPhysicsBody",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " protocol, which",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "allows RealityKit’s physics simulation to compute behavior in response to forces acting upon the body,",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "following basic rules of Newtonian mechanics.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "Note the following when considering applying a non-uniform scale to an entity:",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "items": [
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "text": "Non-uniform scaling is applicable only to box, convex mesh and triangle mesh collision shapes.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "text": "Non-uniform scaling is not supported for all other types of collision shapes. In this case the scale.x",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": " ",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "value is duplicated to the scale’s y and z components as well to force scale uniformity based on the x component.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "text": "If the entity has a non-uniform scale assigned to its transform then that entity should not",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": " ",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "have any descendants assigned that contain rotations in their transforms. A good rule of thumb is to",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": " ",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "assign the non-uniform scale to the entity that has the collision shape, and avoid adding children below",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": " ",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "that entity.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            }
          ],
          "type": "unorderedList"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            {
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "text": "Model entities have a physics body component by default.",
                  "type": "text"
                }
              ],
              "type": "paragraph"
            }
          ],
          "name": "Note",
          "style": "note",
          "type": "aside"
        }
      ],
      "kind": "content"
    }
  ],
